# Bank Loan Model Monitoring with Airflow and Docker

End-to-end MLOps portfolio project that monitors a bank loan eligibility classification model using **Python, PostgreSQL, Airflow, Docker, scikit-learn, drift checks, deployment reporting, and Slack alerts**.

This project is designed as a Canadian banking and finance analytics portfolio project. It demonstrates how a data scientist or risk analytics analyst can move beyond one-time model training and build a repeatable monitoring workflow for model performance, data quality, data drift, and model governance.

> **Responsible-use note:** This project is a decision-support and monitoring workflow. It does not claim to automate real loan approvals or declines. Real lending systems require governance, fairness testing, adverse-action explainability, regulatory review, and human oversight.

---

## Why This Project Matters

A model that performs well during development can fail silently after deployment when new borrower profiles, credit conditions, data collection rules, or product strategies change. In banking, this creates business and governance risk. This project answers a practical production question:

**Is the current batch of loan application data still similar enough to the reference training data, and is the model still reliable enough to remain deployed?**

The pipeline fetches loan application batches from PostgreSQL, performs data sanity checks, engineers features, trains candidate models, selects a champion model, monitors drift, writes deployment reports, and sends Airflow/Slack alerts when review or retraining is recommended.

