## Why This Is Recruiter-Friendly for Canadian Finance Roles

Canadian banking and finance analytics roles frequently emphasize Python, SQL, data quality, BI/reporting communication, model validation, MLOps, Docker/Airflow-style orchestration, and stakeholder-ready documentation. This project is structured to show those skills together in one business narrative instead of presenting isolated notebooks.

This repository is especially relevant to roles such as:

- Data Scientist, Banking Analytics
- Risk Analytics Analyst
- Credit Risk Analyst
- Model Risk / Model Monitoring Analyst
- Data Analyst, Financial Services
- MLOps / ML Platform Analyst
- BI and Reporting Analyst with Python/SQL exposure

---

## Governance and Limitations

- The included sample dataset is for portfolio demonstration only.
- Raw production data, credentials, and trained binary artifacts should not be committed to GitHub.
- Model outputs should support analyst review, not automated lending decisions.
- A real bank implementation would require fairness testing, data lineage controls, model validation sign-off, adverse-action reason-code review, and production access controls.

